post_cb({"bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_3934862_3934947_0": {"length": 8, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 5490}, "so_3934862_3934947_1": {"length": 11, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 5509}}, "n3337": {"so_3934862_3934947_0": {"length": 8, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 5276}, "so_3934862_3934947_1": {"length": 11, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 5295}}, "n4659": {"so_3934862_3934947_0": {"length": 7, "quality": 0.875, "section_id": 6924}, "so_3934862_3934947_1": {"length": 11, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 6944}}}, "3934947": {"Id": "3934947", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<ul>\n<li>7.3.3 The using declaration</li>\n</ul>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_3934862_3934947_0\">A using-declaration introduces a name into the declarative region in which the using-declaration appears.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>And, since someone asked in a comment about <code>using namespace</code>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>7.3.4 Using directive</li>\n</ul>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_3934862_3934947_1\">A using-directive shall not appear in class scope, but may appear in namespace scope or in block scope.</p>\n</blockquote>\n", "LastEditorUserId": "12711", "LastActivityDate": "2010-10-14T15:44:01.183", "Score": "4", "CreationDate": "2010-10-14T15:38:58.170", "ParentId": "3934862", "CommentCount": "0", "LastEditDate": "2010-10-14T15:44:01.183", "OwnerUserId": "12711"}, "3934878": {"Id": "3934878", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>Yes, it's legal. In fact, it's preferred over doing it at file scope...</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2010-10-14T15:31:14.877", "Score": "5", "CreationDate": "2010-10-14T15:31:14.877", "ParentId": "3934862", "CommentCount": "3", "OwnerUserId": "63832"}, "3934862": {"ViewCount": "829", "Body": "<p>My question is pretty much the title. \nExample</p>\n<pre><code>#include &lt;iostream&gt;\n\nint main()\n{\n   using std::cout; //legal?\n   { \n      using std::cin; //legal?\n   }\n}\n</code></pre>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "3934947", "Title": "Can a using-declaration appear at block/function scope?", "CreationDate": "2010-10-14T15:29:55.680", "Id": "3934862", "CommentCount": "9", "LastEditDate": "2010-10-14T15:41:00.967", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "149392", "LastActivityDate": "2010-10-14T15:44:01.183", "Score": "2", "OwnerUserId": "469935", "Tags": "<c++>", "AnswerCount": "3"}, "3934881": {"Id": "3934881", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>Why didn't you test it? It works alright.</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2010-10-14T15:31:27.777", "Score": "0", "CreationDate": "2010-10-14T15:31:27.777", "ParentId": "3934862", "CommentCount": "1", "OwnerUserId": "308668"}});